            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">Linguistic field recordings made at Woodstock Reserve, New Brunswick, Canada, in June 1959. A reading of Malecite words and their English equivalents for multiple varieties and groupings of animals and plants, fish, dwellings, canoes and other water craft, hunting &amp; fishing, and numbers &amp; measures. The final 6 minutes of the recording consist of a reading from from Joseph Laurent's "New Familiar Abenakis and English Dialogues" (St-Francis, Quebec, 1884).</abstract>
            <physdesc id="ref2" label="General Physical Description note">1 sound tape reel (1 hr., 11 min.) : analog, 7 1/2 ips, half track, mono ; 7 in.</physdesc>
